{{Race}}
<!--Race defined, described, and overall "pro's" of the concept:-->
'''Race''' refers to classifications of [[human]]s into [[population]]s or [[Group (sociology)|group]]s based on various factors, such as their [[culture]], [[language]], social practice or [[Heritability|heritable]] characteristics.<ref>{{Cite web|title=
race |year=2010 |publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica Online |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/488030/race |accessdate=2010-08-03}}</ref> As a [[Race (biology)|biological term]], race denotes [[Genetic divergence|genetically divergent]] human [[population]]s that can be marked by common [[Phenotype|phenotypic]] traits.<ref>''See:''
